The Herald Sports Reporter ZIMBABWE international Knox Mutizwa was honoured by South African Premiership football side Lamontville Golden Arrows at the weekend. Mutizwa, who is the team’s all-time leading goal scorer, was celebrated before their game against Royal Aim in which he scored again, to take his tally to 51 goals. However, the Durban-based outfit lost the match 1-2. Mutizwa surpassed Mabhudi Khenyeza’s previous record of 39 goals in 2021.